I have this code that creates different types of notifications (email, SMS, push). Right now I have a big switch statement in my NotificationService class. Every time I add a new notification type, I have to modify the service. How should I restructure this?

```typescript
class NotificationService {
  send(type: string, message: string, recipient: string) {
    switch(type) {
      case 'email':
        const email = new EmailNotifier();
        email.send(recipient, message);
        break;
      case 'sms':
        const sms = new SMSNotifier();
        sms.send(recipient, message);
        break;
      case 'push':
        const push = new PushNotifier();
        push.send(recipient, message);
        break;
    }
  }
}
```

